                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Wäldä ʾIyäsus</persName>Wäldä ʾIyäsus is mentioned as the scribe in the concluding supplications of Texts II (fol. 49va) and IV (fol. 79rb).<date>Beginning of the 20th century</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting tends to small, broadly spaced letters. It appears irregular throughout the Ms. and changes from careful and neat, with upright and slender letters (cp., fols. 10r, 30r, 35r, 37v) to mediocre, with irregularly slanted (right and left sloping) letters and forked hook vowel markers (cp., fols. 3r-9r, 22r-25v).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
